The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, February 19, 2004 				 Ravs royal Rajasthan secret
 SUDHANSHU MISHRA				 	 Bride to be: Raveena TandonJaipur, Feb. 18: Raveena Tandon is convinced she was a Rajasthani queen in her last birth, so her family has planned a royal wedding for the actress in the city of palaces.																								Main pichhle janam mein Rajasthan ki rani thi, sister-in-law Rakhi quoted the actress as telling her. Immediately, word got around in the family that the Mast Mast girl wanted to be married like a princess. The venues that were then being considered  Bangalore and Hyderabad among them  were dropped and arrangements were made for the February 22 wedding in Udaipur.																								Raveena will tie the knot with producer Anil Thadani at Jagmandir, an island palace in Lake Pichola. The palace, which served as a refuge for Prince Khurram in 1623 and is said to have inspired him to build the Taj Mahal when he became Emperor Shah Jahan, is let out for weddings by the HRH Group of Hotels. The group, owned by the Udaipur royal family, offers regal wedding packages.																								The sangeet sammelan will be held on Friday, followed by the mehendi rasm on Saturday at City Palace. 																								The wedding and the reception will be held on Sunday. Salman Khan, Shah Rukh Khan and wife Gauri, Hrithik Roshan and wife Suzanne, Rani Mukherjee and Govinda have confirmed they will attend, sources said. 																								Members of the Tandon and Thadani families are already in Udaipur. The bride and her father are reaching tomorrow. 																								If the wedding is royal, the honeymoons a secret. Neither Raveena nor her groom knows where her brother Rajiv and Rakhi have planned to send them. This is the honeymoon gift package and has been kept top secret, the brother of the bride said.
